                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Nov. 19: IDBI Fortis Life Insurance Company hopes to break even by 2015. The firm started operations last year. We aim to break even in the next seven years hopefully, G.V. Nageswara Rao, managing director of IDBI Fortis Life Insurance Company, said at the launch of its Incomesurance Endowment and Money Back plan.           
	Business index                  
	 Mumbai, Nov. 19: Business confidence in India has bounced back on improving economic conditions and has surpassed the level prevailing prior to the financial meltdown, according to a survey by NCAER and Mastercard. The index went up 21 per cent in October at 143.7 points against 119.9 a year ago.                            
	 New Delhi, Nov. 19: The government said the auction of coal blocks for captive use would take place this fiscal. A bill to allow competitive bidding is likely to be introduced in the current session of Parliament. The auction policy will come up in the next 2-4 months.                            
	 New Delhi, Nov. 19: The Anil Ambani group today accused the government of being party to the conspiracy with Mukesh Ambani firm RIL to destroy it but dropped its opposition to the petroleum ministry putting its stand before the Supreme Court.                            
	 Mumbai, Nov. 19: Suzlon Energy will sell its 35 per cent stake in Belgian firm Hansen Transmissions through a book-building process.
                                                                                                                          
